Packaging
=========

1. Env installation
  1. LXC
  2. extra packages
  3. Web Server/CGI or Dialog ?
2. Fill your information
  1. Name
  2. 2-LETTERS abbrev
  3. upload location
  4. upload schema
3. Create a new package
  1. package name
  2. home page
  3. download page
  4. choose a method to determine the latest stable version
  5. accept or force a version
  6. choose a download url schema
  7. choose "noarch" or "archdep"
  8. choose a SLKBUILD schema
  9. determine deps and build deps
  10. write build process
  11. write package process
4. Check for new version
5. Go the home page or download page
6. Schedule a package to be built in a container (version, arch)
7. Show queue
8. Show result
9. Post resource on Tracker

